  "prompt": "Which are the most romantic movies?",
  "response": "Romantic movies are a beloved genre, and several have stood out over the years for their compelling storytelling, captivating performances, and emotional impact. Here are some of the most romantic movies:\n\n1. **\"The Notebook\" (2004)** - Starring Ryan Gosling and Rachel McAdams, this film is based on Nicholas Sparks' novel and tells the story of a passionate love affair that spans decades.\n\n2. **\"Titanic\" (1997)** - Directed by James Cameron and starring Leonardo DiCaprio and Kate Winslet, this epic romance set against the backdrop of the ill-fated Titanic is a timeless classic.\n\n3. **\"Pride and Prejudice\" (2005)** - This adaptation of Jane Austen's beloved novel stars Keira Knightley and Matthew Macfadyen, and captures the romance between Elizabeth Bennet and Mr. Darcy.\n\n4. **\"La La Land\" (2016)** - Starring Emma Stone and Ryan Gosling, this modern musical explores the highs and lows of a romantic relationship set against the backdrop of Los Angeles.\n\n5. **\"Before Sunrise\" (1995)** - Directed by Richard Linklater and starring Ethan Hawke and Julie Delpy, this film is the first in a trilogy that beautifully captures the connection between two strangers who meet in Vienna.\n\n6. **\"Casablanca\" (1942)** - Starring Humphrey Bogart and Ingrid Bergman, this classic film set during World War II is renowned for its timeless romance and iconic dialogue.\n\n7. **\"Gone with the Wind\" (1939)** - Starring Vivien Leigh and Clark Gable, this epic historical romance set during the Civil War remains one of the most enduring love stories in cinematic history.\n\n8. **\"Eternal Sunshine of the Spotless Mind\" (2004)** - Starring Jim Carrey and Kate Winslet, this unique film explores the complexities of love and memory in a poignant and imaginative way.\n\n9. **\"Romeo + Juliet\" (1996)** - Directed by Baz Luhrmann and starring Leonardo DiCaprio and Claire Danes, this modern adaptation of Shakespeare's classic tragedy is visually stunning and emotionally charged.\n\n10. **\"Notting Hill\" (1999)** - Starring Julia Roberts and Hugh Grant, this charming romantic comedy tells the story of an unlikely romance between a famous actress and a humble bookstore owner.\n\nThese movies have resonated with audiences for their ability to capture the essence of love, in all its forms and complexities.",
